Nigerian thespian Femi Adebayo was recently hosted to a surprise private screening of his new movie, King of Thieves, by StarTimes. Adebayo, a leading ambassador for the pay-TV company, was caught unawares when StarTimes management held a private screening for his new epic movie at Silverbird Cinemas. The star actor was showered with accolades for the originality of the story and costume. The epic action-thriller was screened with Nollywood stars, and movie critics like StarTimes CEO, Alex Jian, Content Director, Viki Liu, Bose Adewara, Lazarus Ibeabuchi, Segun Arinze, Yaw, Kate Effiong, and Abubakar Yakubu among others,  in attendance.   Nollywood suffers from lack of structure, says Dakore     Asa: I don’t want to be a stranger in Nigeria     Omawumi, others pick six winners as Quickteller Barz and…   An excited Adebayo shared the inspiration behind the film saying, “the inspiration behind this movie is to showcase the creativity of the Yoruba culture to the entire world. Cultural folklore and true epic films are gradually dying, yet it is full of beautiful stories.” Speaking at the event, Alex Jian said, “StarTimes is proud to associate with Femi Adebayo, who is also our brand ambassador. An outstanding project like this tells African stories from an African perspective. Femi Adebayo is notable for setting standards in the industry. Our business strategy is tied to the growth of quality local content. This is what our audience is craving and we are strongly committed to this through investments, support, and celebrations of notable works.” Continuing, he said, “This informs why we have taken the partnership with AMAA a notch higher. Currently, StarTimes-AMAA Short Film Festival is ongoing with over $10,000 prizes reserved for winners.” King of Thieves features Toyin Abraham, Lateef Adedimeji, Adebayo Salami, Broda Shagi, Femi Adebayo, Segun Arinze, among other A-list actors.